result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin M. Anderson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant appeared with counsel SPD William Poss.  DA Gerald Fox appears for the State.  DA Fox states there is no restitution and victim notification has been complied with.  Joint recommendation for plea and sentencing.  He previously plead to 14CF47 - only needs sentencing on this case.  Judge reviewed charges/penalties/waiver of rights/elements.  Guilty pleas entered as follows:  14CF189 Count 1, amended to Misd. bailjumping - Guilty plea; 15CM25, Counts 1 & 2 - Guilty pleas; 14CF192, Counts 1 amended to misd. theft & Count 2 - Guilty pleas with Count 3 dismissed and read-in.  Court finds the defendant understands the proceedings, pleas are entered and rights waived knowingly, voluntarily, and intelligently.  Defendant is found guilty of charges as amended or stated.  Defendant speaks.  Sentence recommendation is adopted and ordered:  Probation for 3 years on each count/case concurrent with following conditions:    Defendant must attend and successfully complete an alcohol assessment and comply with any recommended treatment.  Defendant is to execute any releases necessary for agent to verify compliance.  Defendant must attend and successfully complete a drug assessment, and comply with any recommended treatment.  Defendant to execute any releases necessary for agent to verify compliance.  The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  Defendant may apply for expungement if probation successfully completed and all court obligations are satisfied.  Defendant may also petition for early release after 2 years if complaint with all probation requirements.  No contact allowed with Nick Thorson.  No access allowed to any financial information of another person except for your own.  Must pay the costs of the action including the DNA surcharge and must supply a DNA sample.
